text: Fernanda Alves (born 29 June 1985) is a volleyball player from Brazil. She was a member of the Brazil women's national volleyball team. == Career == She participated in the 2005 FIVB Women's World Grand Champions Cup, and the 2017 FIVB Beach Volleyball World Championships. ==Clubs== * Fluminense FC (1999–2001) * ACF/Campos (2001–2004) * São Caetano (2004–2005) * Brasil Telecom (2005–2006) * Pinheiros (2006–2007) * Daejeon KGC (2007–2008) * Pallavolo Cesena (2008–2010) * Sport Recife (2009–2010) * Praia Clube (2010–2011) * Vôlei Futuro (2011–2012) == References == == External links == * Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:Brazilian women's volleyball players Category:LGBT volleyball players
title: Fernanda Alves
